1
00:01:30,230 --> 00:01:34,940
[Our Dazzling Days]

2
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:37,770
[Episode 1]

3
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:43,120
[2007 Japan]

4
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:46,430
10 seconds left in the 5th round.

5
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:48,479
Can Tanaka hold on?

6
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:52,840
Rear hand! Miura threw a heavy punch!

7
00:01:52,860 --> 00:01:56,060
Tanaka is down! Miura wins!

8
00:01:56,539 --> 00:01:59,009
The challenger for the next match
is Miyamura Masao.

9
00:01:59,009 --> 00:02:01,610
He will face Zhang Xiaoman from China,

10
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:04,640
who is riding a ten-fight winning streak.

11
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,650
Zhang Xiaoman
must be taken down in the 3rd round.

12
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,150
The gym has put

13
00:02:09,169 --> 00:02:10,699
all its funds on this fight.

14
00:02:11,220 --> 00:02:13,340
No other outcome is acceptable.

15
00:02:15,320 --> 00:02:16,430
The stakes this time

16
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:18,740
have broken all previous records.

17
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:19,800
Yes.

18
00:02:20,430 --> 00:02:22,160
Everything has been arranged.

19
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,910
Xiaoman,

20
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:27,560
have you heard this saying?

21
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:30,840
"Insanity is doing the same thing

22
00:02:30,860 --> 00:02:32,260
over and over

23
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:35,360
and expecting different results."

24
00:02:36,820 --> 00:02:39,980
I think you and I have been doing

25
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,640
the same thing all along.

26
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,710
Maybe it's time for us to wake up

27
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:47,030
and live a different life.

28
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:17,410
First up is Zhang Xiaoman

29
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:20,400
from KOB Boxing Gym in China!

30
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,630
Xiaoman! Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

31
00:03:22,630 --> 00:03:25,310
Go, Xiaoman!

32
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:27,150
Xiaoman! Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

33
00:03:27,150 --> 00:03:30,840
Next is the famous Miyamura Masao.

34
00:03:31,910 --> 00:03:35,240
He was knocked down
by Zhang Xiaoman in a previous match.

35
00:03:35,470 --> 00:03:38,560
This time it's his revenge fight.

36
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,040
Get Yu Qiangbei here!

37
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:28,760
Yes!

38
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,390
Boss, we didn't find Yu Qiangbei.

39
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:41,000
What?

40
00:04:41,409 --> 00:04:42,340
Get out of my way!

41
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,000
Xiaoman,

42
00:04:49,510 --> 00:04:51,070
didn't Yu Qiangbei
make things clear to you?

43
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:52,890
Those who don't follow the rules
end up in Tokyo Bay!

44
00:04:52,890 --> 00:04:54,090
Translate it for him.

45
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:54,890
Xiaoman,

46
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,120
he wants you to lose.

47
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:57,390
He's asking if you
don't understand the rules.

48
00:04:57,390 --> 00:04:59,570
He says your family
will be collecting your body.

49
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:00,770
I never throw a fight.

50
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,320
He doesn't throw fights.

51
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:07,310
I've bet everything on this match.

52
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:09,600
You must lose this fight.

53
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:11,200
Please.

54
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:13,750
Xiaoman!

55
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:18,480
Name your price—I'll pay!

56
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:21,800
Start!

57
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:10,520
The winner is Zhang Xiaoman!

58
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:32,240
Xiaoman! Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

59
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,560
Stop! Catch him!

60
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,830
Pay up! Stop! Hurry!

61
00:06:49,750 --> 00:06:53,870
Don't run! Stop! Get him!

62
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:54,950
Stop!

63
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:57,920
Stop! Don't run!

64
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:13,920
Stop!

65
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:19,240
Don't hit me! Don't hit me!

66
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:27,190
Xiaoman,

67
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:30,800
why did you team up with Yu Qiangbei?

68
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:34,870
You think you can escape?

69
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:38,500
The money. The money.

70
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,330
I'll give it all back to you.

71
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,430
Spare me.

72
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:45,630
I don't throw fights.

73
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:48,360
Don't hit me.

74
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:51,270
Get him!

75
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:19,800
My name is Zhang Xiaoman.

76
00:08:19,950 --> 00:08:23,330
I was born in a massive factory
in the western suburbs of Tiecheng.

77
00:08:23,330 --> 00:08:25,500
We call it Western Tiecheng.

78
00:08:23,660 --> 00:08:26,710
[East Chemical Plant]

79
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,920
Here, the factory and the residential area
are combined,

80
00:08:27,010 --> 00:08:31,100
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

81
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:29,360
with all the necessary facilities.

82
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,950
In the late 1960s,

83
00:08:31,310 --> 00:08:32,809
the Fifth Industrial Ministry rushed

84
00:08:32,809 --> 00:08:34,140
to relocate our factory

85
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:37,679
from the China-Soviet border
to a remote valley in Northeast China,

86
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:40,140
and hastily built this "Western Tiecheng."

87
00:08:40,909 --> 00:08:41,909
My grandparents

88
00:08:42,030 --> 00:08:43,429
came here just like that.

89
00:08:44,270 --> 00:08:46,800
That generation of workers,
full of passion,

90
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,970
carried the backbone
of the Third Front Construction

91
00:08:48,970 --> 00:08:51,090
amid the roar of the machines.

92
00:08:52,910 --> 00:08:55,550
Outsiders called us
the "East Chemical Plant,"

93
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:56,750
but they had no idea
what we actually produced—

94
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,630
it was a secret unit.

95
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:02,550
Only after the 1980s, when military
industries shifted to civilian use,

96
00:09:02,550 --> 00:09:05,410
did the factory gradually
lose its veil of secrecy.

97
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,960
People then realized that

98
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:08,030
our factory

99
00:09:08,150 --> 00:09:11,280
was one of the nation's
top gunpowder production bases.

100
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:13,760
All the children here were proud of it.

101
00:09:14,980 --> 00:09:16,410
This is my home.

102
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,360
Like most factory kids,

103
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:22,120
I was born in the staff hospital

104
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:25,120
and grew up running wild

105
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:27,650
[East Chemical Plant, 1990]

106
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:27,010
through the factory area.

107
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,390
Zhang Xiaoman, stay right there!

108
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:30,320
You little brat!

109
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:31,220
You've actually...

110
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:32,890
You've actually learned to lie to me now?

111
00:09:32,890 --> 00:09:34,660
Playing these little tricks on me, huh?

112
00:09:34,660 --> 00:09:36,020
I'll smack you silly!

113
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,500
Stay right there!

114
00:09:38,280 --> 00:09:39,330
Come back here, Zhang Xiaoman!

115
00:09:39,330 --> 00:09:40,490
Give me back my shoe!

116
00:09:46,820 --> 00:09:47,430
Here!

117
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,960
Dad, I'm leaving!

118
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,370
I'll be waiting for you!

119
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:54,080
Xia Lei, just you wait!

120
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,720
We just moved in
and you're already causing trouble.

121
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:59,180
We brought all this stuff over
from the old factory, bit by bit.

122
00:10:04,820 --> 00:10:05,340
Fine.

123
00:10:06,670 --> 00:10:08,820
This new boy is Xia Lei.

124
00:10:09,260 --> 00:10:10,720
His mother worked at the staff hospital,

125
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,550
and his father
was a driver in the transportation team.

126
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:14,790
We met during an escape.

127
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:17,670
Back then, I watched this quiet boy

128
00:10:17,690 --> 00:10:19,910
following behind me, huffing and puffing,

129
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:21,370
so honest it made me laugh.

130
00:10:21,910 --> 00:10:23,360
Who would have thought

131
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,480
we'd become the closest of friends.

132
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:37,960
Who are you?

133
00:10:38,670 --> 00:10:40,070
Why are you following me?

134
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,220
I'm not following you.

135
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,320
My mom beat me up

136
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:47,220
and then kicked me out.

137
00:10:48,460 --> 00:10:49,480
I don't know what to do.

138
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,010
So I'm just walking around.

139
00:10:52,030 --> 00:10:53,030
Then come with me.

140
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:55,690
Come on.

141
00:10:57,670 --> 00:10:58,270
Let's go!

142
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:02,940
Is it safe here?

143
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:05,150
It's safe. They don't usually come here.

144
00:11:05,150 --> 00:11:06,680
And this place is spacious.

145
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,630
If they come, we can see them

146
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:09,830
and run away anytime.

147
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,100
Where are you from?

148
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:12,630
Are you here visiting relatives?

149
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,630
No, I used to live in the old factory.

150
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:15,990
Now we've moved here.

151
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,600
No wonder I haven't seen you before.

152
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,360
What's your name?

153
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:20,560
What grade are you in?

154
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:22,150
My name is Xia Lei.

155
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,250
I'm in 4th grade.

156
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:24,780
What a coincidence.

157
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:26,790
Your surname is Xia too?

158
00:11:26,790 --> 00:11:27,910
No, I'm not a Xia.

159
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,340
My name is Zhang Xiaoman.

160
00:11:29,340 --> 00:11:30,540
I'm also in 4th grade.

161
00:11:30,630 --> 00:11:33,090
If anyone bullies you,
just mention my name.

162
00:11:33,530 --> 00:11:34,240
Come.

163
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,640
Let's go play over there.

164
00:11:36,510 --> 00:11:37,350
Are you crazy?

165
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:40,000
You need to hold it like this
and eat it this way.

166
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,340
It has the fragrance of corn husks.

167
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:42,940
And it won't burn your hands.

168
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,150
Fellow workers,

169
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:51,600
this is the East Integrated Chemical Plant
broadcasting station.

170
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,450
The golden autumn brings cool air
and sweet-scented osmanthus.

171
00:11:54,450 --> 00:11:55,790
During the recently concluded

172
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:58,270
16-day Beijing Asian Games,

173
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:59,960
we all witnessed

174
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,240
the fighting spirit of our athletes

175
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,600
and felt proud of their achievements.

176
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:07,300
Now for a vaccination announcement.

177
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,480
All primary school students

178
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:11,390
born in 1980 must be accompanied

179
00:12:11,490 --> 00:12:12,880
by a parent

180
00:12:12,930 --> 00:12:15,600
to get vaccinated at the staff hospital
this week.

181
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,440
Come on, class is starting.

182
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:17,370
Take your seats.

183
00:12:17,390 --> 00:12:18,240
The teacher is here!

184
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,350
Put that down quickly!

185
00:12:19,350 --> 00:12:20,350
Stop running.

186
00:12:25,590 --> 00:12:27,470
Alright, everyone.

187
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:31,320
This is Xia Lei.

188
00:12:31,550 --> 00:12:33,200
His parents were transferred for work,

189
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,840
so he's been placed in our class.

190
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,790
Let's give him a warm welcome.

191
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:39,510
Xia Lei!

192
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,600
Xia Lei,

193
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,600
please introduce yourself.

194
00:12:48,630 --> 00:12:49,630
My name is Xia Lei.

195
00:12:53,030 --> 00:12:53,890
Anything else?

196
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,750
I'm male.

197
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,860
That's enough.

198
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:02,970
We got it. Well...

199
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,000
Go take that seat over there, okay?

200
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,190
Go ahead.

201
00:13:08,150 --> 00:13:08,790
Here.

202
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:14,360
Since we have a new student joining us,

203
00:13:14,550 --> 00:13:17,550
I want to emphasize
our confidentiality rules again.

204
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:20,590
Our factory requires everyone
to maintain secrecy,

205
00:13:20,590 --> 00:13:22,960
and primary school students
are no exception.

206
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:25,000
If you visit relatives in other places

207
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,240
and your relatives ask you

208
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,790
what our factory produces,

209
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:31,390
you must answer
"pesticides and fertilizers."

210
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:34,670
Nothing else should be mentioned,
understand?

211
00:13:34,790 --> 00:13:36,000
Yes.

212
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,840
Ma'am.

213
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:38,000
Didn't you tell us

214
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,630
that we should be honest and trustworthy?

215
00:13:39,630 --> 00:13:41,150
We shouldn't lie.

216
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,600
You should be honest with your family

217
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:44,860
and the organization.

218
00:13:45,290 --> 00:13:47,870
But with enemies and spies,
of course you must keep secrets.

219
00:13:47,870 --> 00:13:48,630
Ma'am, tell me,

220
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:50,240
if my second great-aunt asks me,

221
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:51,870
should I tell her the truth?

222
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:54,610
Your second great-aunt?
Better not tell her.

223
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:56,480
Distant relatives don't count as family.

224
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:58,320
They might even be enemies or spies.

225
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,440
Ma'am, why would distant relatives

226
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:01,170
possibly be enemies and spies?

227
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:01,910
Because

228
00:14:01,930 --> 00:14:04,330
we don't know distant relatives very well.

229
00:14:04,360 --> 00:14:05,760
Who's making that sound?

230
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:06,980
Then why couldn't close relatives

231
00:14:06,980 --> 00:14:08,650
be enemies or spies?

232
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,390
Zhang Xiaoman,

233
00:14:10,790 --> 00:14:12,240
are you deliberately being difficult?

234
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,840
Just do as I say

235
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,700
and don't ask so many questions.

236
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:15,910
But ma'am, look,

237
00:14:16,030 --> 00:14:17,480
my grandma is a close relative of mine,
right?

238
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:18,570
If I tell my grandma,

239
00:14:18,570 --> 00:14:19,840
and she tells her sister,

240
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,200
isn't that the same?

241
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,300
Zhang Xiaoman,

242
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:25,790
Are you stupid

243
00:14:25,790 --> 00:14:27,390
or are you arguing on purpose?

244
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:28,250
How about this?

245
00:14:28,370 --> 00:14:29,370
Let me tell you.

246
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:30,770
Whenever someone asks you anything,

247
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:32,500
just say "I'm a little piglet."

248
00:14:32,630 --> 00:14:34,030
"I know nothing but eat."

249
00:14:34,030 --> 00:14:34,840
Got it?

250
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:39,720
Xia Lei, where's your hometown?

251
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:41,750
Before, it was Heilongjiang...

252
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:42,880
You okay, Dongdong?

253
00:14:46,200 --> 00:14:46,860
Step aside!

254
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:50,320
Who's that?

255
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:52,870
That's our factory's celebrity,

256
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:53,750
Mr. Ding.

257
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:56,870
In our factory,
you need to avoid two things: big trucks,

258
00:14:56,870 --> 00:14:58,200
and Mr. Ding.

259
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,480
Why?

260
00:14:59,630 --> 00:15:01,960
Mr. Ding fought in the war

261
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:03,560
and was even a platoon leader.

262
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:05,230
So is everyone afraid of him?

263
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:06,080
No.

264
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:08,530
Mr. Ding and his fiancée had an agreement

265
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,360
to get married
when he returned from the war.

266
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,140
But who would've known

267
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:12,390
that just when they were about to win,

268
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,870
the enemy's last bullet

269
00:15:13,870 --> 00:15:14,840
wounded him.

270
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,130
So everyone sympathizes with him?

271
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,150
Not exactly.

272
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:20,080
After Mr. Ding got injured,

273
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,740
he needs a monthly injection.

274
00:15:21,790 --> 00:15:23,390
But it only lasts for an hour.

275
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,440
During that hour,

276
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:26,600
no one dares to stop Mr. Ding,

277
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,630
who is in a hurry
to go home to take care of his "business".

278
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:29,460
There's gonna be a show.

279
00:15:29,460 --> 00:15:30,520
What's happening?

280
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,750
Hey, you on the bike!

281
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:43,350
Don't run!

282
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,480
Stop right there!

283
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:46,010
Do you know who you slapped?

284
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:47,910
A wise dog doesn't block the road.
Don't you know?

285
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:49,010
If you delay me one minute,

286
00:15:49,010 --> 00:15:50,670
tomorrow I'll slap all three of you!

287
00:15:50,670 --> 00:15:52,080
That's badass!

288
00:15:52,270 --> 00:15:52,910
Get lost!

289
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:55,030
How dare you talk like that?

290
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:56,690
What kind of attitude is this?

291
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:58,120
Everyone, be the judge!

292
00:15:58,150 --> 00:15:59,790
Just because someone blocked him,

293
00:15:59,790 --> 00:16:02,670
he actually dared to slap Director Meng,
who just transferred here!

294
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,270
Look, that's my brother,

295
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,920
the big boss of our East Chemical Plant.

296
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,660
He's really tough.

297
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:13,840
What are you guys doing here?

298
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,500
We're just watching the show.

299
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:19,510
Have you learned roller skating yet?

300
00:16:19,510 --> 00:16:20,060
Almost.

301
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,600
I've fallen enough times.

302
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,910
Once you've got it down,
I'll get you a pair of skates.

303
00:16:23,910 --> 00:16:24,720
Thanks, Da.

304
00:16:24,940 --> 00:16:27,030
Da, can you get me a pair too?

305
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:28,880
What do you need them for?

306
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:30,360
How many times have I told you

307
00:16:30,360 --> 00:16:31,600
not to hang around here after school?

308
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,320
Got it?

309
00:16:32,990 --> 00:16:33,990
Go home and study.

310
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:38,670
Bye, Da.

311
00:16:50,830 --> 00:16:51,560
You're back?

312
00:16:52,750 --> 00:16:54,510
Dad, you didn't go drinking?

313
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:56,080
I did.

314
00:16:59,270 --> 00:17:00,600
Uncle Wang's wife

315
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,390
dragged him away.

316
00:17:02,980 --> 00:17:03,910
We wrapped it up.

317
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:12,310
I'm going to my room to take a nap.

318
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,130
Clean this up and get some rest early.

319
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:19,869
Sure.

320
00:17:44,880 --> 00:17:46,270
When Mom was around,

321
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,600
My dad was the

322
00:17:48,620 --> 00:17:50,880
best level-eight fitter in the factory.

323
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:54,080
Even his workshop director
had to respect him.

324
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:56,000
But after my mom left,

325
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,880
he became a "level-eight alcoholic,"

326
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:01,270
always glued to his bottle.

327
00:18:01,670 --> 00:18:04,000
Whenever he got drunk,
he'd go on a rampage

328
00:18:04,130 --> 00:18:06,370
and hit me with his electrician's belt.

329
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,340
I often wondered,

330
00:18:10,410 --> 00:18:11,870
if my mom hadn't left,

331
00:18:12,350 --> 00:18:13,920
would my dad still be

332
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,750
a level-eight fitter,

333
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,880
and would I have been spared
from being beaten every day?

334
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:20,880
The 24th anniversary celebration

335
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:24,220
of the East Integrated Chemical Plant
is coming soon.

336
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:23,930
[Congratulations on the 24th Anniversary]

337
00:18:23,930 --> 00:18:25,310
[of East Integrated Chemical Plant's
Founding]

338
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:27,440
All staff are encouraged to participate.

339
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:28,750
Line up!

340
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:32,390
Come on. Look at me.

341
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:34,370
Straighten your lines.

342
00:18:34,370 --> 00:18:35,650
Dress right, dress!

343
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:36,880
Dress!

344
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:38,000
Eyes front!

345
00:18:38,070 --> 00:18:38,760
Front!

346
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:40,920
Very good.

347
00:18:41,270 --> 00:18:43,170
See how well Wang Dongdong is doing?

348
00:18:43,170 --> 00:18:45,000
Alright, today everyone

349
00:18:45,030 --> 00:18:46,160
has done very well.

350
00:18:46,590 --> 00:18:47,680
Did you all watch

351
00:18:47,680 --> 00:18:49,200
the Beijing Asian Games closing ceremony

352
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,000
last night?

353
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,440
Yes!

354
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,240
Was it good?

355
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,480
Yes!

356
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,270
You all

357
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:56,510
should be like those performers
at the closing ceremony,

358
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:58,750
unified and full of energy,

359
00:18:58,790 --> 00:19:01,000
when you appear
at our factory celebration.

360
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:01,590
Alright?

361
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:02,700
Yes!

362
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:08,240
Very good.

363
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,590
Let me tell you something.

364
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:12,190
Don't just stand there
watching the fun later.

365
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,510
When you see the director,

366
00:19:13,510 --> 00:19:15,790
you need to apologize properly.

367
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:19,680
Ms. Zhang,

368
00:19:19,860 --> 00:19:21,270
please keep an eye on the children.

369
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:22,200
Don't let them run around.

370
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,640
Your performance is second on the program.

371
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:24,480
Alright, Secretary Liu.

372
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:25,880
Don't worry. Come on, kids.

373
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,590
Xiaodan,

374
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,000
you sing very well.

375
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,560
Sing your best. Go for it.

376
00:19:29,620 --> 00:19:30,420
Sure, sir.

377
00:19:30,730 --> 00:19:31,790
Line up, everyone.

378
00:19:34,200 --> 00:19:35,060
Director Meng.

379
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:38,170
Mr. Ding?

380
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:40,490
Wh-What can I do for you?

381
00:19:41,750 --> 00:19:43,160
It's nothing important.

382
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:47,350
Just the other day, I...

383
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,350
Director Meng, Chief Engineer Yan,

384
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:50,920
it's your turn to go on stage.

385
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,510
Everything's ready. Please.

386
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:54,640
Mr. Ding, we'll talk later.

387
00:19:54,940 --> 00:19:55,440
I need to go on stage now.

388
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,700
Alright, you go ahead.

389
00:20:02,270 --> 00:20:03,790
Good afternoon, everyone.

390
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:04,590
I'm very pleased

391
00:20:04,020 --> 00:20:07,410
[Congratulations on the 24th Anniversary]

392
00:20:04,590 --> 00:20:06,190
that we can gather here today

393
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:07,720
to celebrate

394
00:20:07,410 --> 00:20:10,800
[of East Integrated Chemical Plant's
Founding]

395
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,440
East Integrated Chemical Plant's

396
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,850
24th birthday.

397
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,070
Bravo!

398
00:20:15,270 --> 00:20:17,680
Next, let's welcome
Director Meng to speak.

399
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,070
Please give him a round of applause!

400
00:20:19,070 --> 00:20:20,640
Bravo!

401
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:24,880
Hello, comrades.

402
00:20:27,710 --> 00:20:31,030
Today marks the 24th anniversary

403
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:32,680
of the East Chemical Plant,

404
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:35,240
and it is also an important moment
for me personally.

405
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:37,640
I'm so thrilled
to join the East Chemical Plant

406
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:38,900
to work with all of you,

407
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,880
to fight alongside you,

408
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,590
and to become

409
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:45,350
part of the East Chemical Plant.

410
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:46,680
Bravo!

411
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:47,970
Ma'am.

412
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,550
-Ma'am, could you sweep later?
-Please don't sweep now.

413
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:50,790
We want to collect some firecrackers.

414
00:20:50,790 --> 00:20:51,680
Fine, go ahead.

415
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:52,640
Thank you, ma'am.

416
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,640
Thank you, ma'am.

417
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:55,200
The next 10 years

418
00:20:55,640 --> 00:20:58,350
will be our decade
of reaching new heights.

419
00:20:58,750 --> 00:20:59,680
All of us

420
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:03,790
will stride proudly together
into the new century!

421
00:21:04,070 --> 00:21:05,550
Bravo!

422
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:11,400
Next is the annual excellence awards
ceremony.

423
00:21:11,610 --> 00:21:13,270
-The award recipients,
-Music!

424
00:21:13,270 --> 00:21:15,400
please come up to receive your awards.

425
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:18,510
Stand in the middle.

426
00:21:18,020 --> 00:21:22,370
♪ The Five-star Red Flag
flutters in the wind ♪

427
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:19,420
-In the middle?
-In the middle.

428
00:21:19,420 --> 00:21:19,860
Okay.

429
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,750
Ding.

430
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:26,490
♪ The song of victory is so loud ♪

431
00:21:26,590 --> 00:21:30,810
♪ It's praising our beloved motherland ♪

432
00:21:30,750 --> 00:21:31,720
Well done, Mr. Zhang.

433
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:34,750
♪ Now embarking on a path
to prosperity and strength ♪

434
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:39,090
♪ It's praising our beloved motherland ♪

435
00:21:39,110 --> 00:21:43,450
♪ Now embarking on a path
to prosperity and strength ♪

436
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:43,050
Mr. Ding, thank you for your hard work.

437
00:21:43,550 --> 00:21:44,540
Director Meng, thank you.

438
00:21:44,060 --> 00:21:48,040
♪ We've crossed the mountains
and the plains ♪

439
00:21:44,920 --> 00:21:46,310
You're so generous.

440
00:21:47,350 --> 00:21:48,510
Even though I offended you,

441
00:21:48,060 --> 00:21:52,040
♪ We've forged through the surging
Yellow River and Yangtze ♪

442
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:51,290
you didn't strip me
of my model worker title.

443
00:21:51,290 --> 00:21:53,380
I apologize to you. I'm sorry.

444
00:21:52,340 --> 00:21:56,420
♪ This vast and beautiful land ♪

445
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:54,490
Mr. Ding,

446
00:21:54,830 --> 00:21:56,680
what are you talking about?

447
00:21:56,620 --> 00:22:00,320
♪ Is our dear hometown ♪

448
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,920
You're a battle hero.

449
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,270
A role model for the East Chemical Plant.

450
00:22:00,340 --> 00:22:03,790
The heroes are standing up

451
00:22:02,350 --> 00:22:03,480
Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

452
00:22:03,850 --> 00:22:04,350
What is it?

453
00:22:04,350 --> 00:22:05,070
Hurry up!

454
00:22:05,510 --> 00:22:07,370
It's Xiaodan's performance now.

455
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:08,200
Already?

456
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:11,340
Performer:
East Chemical Plant Elementary School,

457
00:22:11,340 --> 00:22:13,550
Class 3, Grade 4. Yan Xiaodan.

458
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:15,610
Here she comes.

459
00:22:24,770 --> 00:22:29,200
♪ Outside the pavilion, by the ancient way

460
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:33,630
♪ Fragrant grass spreads to the sky,
green and gay ♪

461
00:22:33,720 --> 00:22:35,240
This little girl singing

462
00:22:34,740 --> 00:22:39,290
♪ Evening wind caresses willows,
flute notes fade ♪

463
00:22:35,350 --> 00:22:36,440
is Yan Xiaodan.

464
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:39,350
She's the only child
of our chief engineer Yan Wenyuan,

465
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:43,840
♪ Beyond the hills,
sunset's glow displayed ♪

466
00:22:39,550 --> 00:22:41,240
born late in his life.

467
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:44,480
Xiaodan didn't inherit
her father's math genes,

468
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:46,790
but she got her mother's gentle beauty.

469
00:22:45,050 --> 00:22:49,390
♪ Far at the edge of sky,
corner of earth ♪

470
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:49,200
Don't be fooled by her quiet demeanor.

471
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,480
All the other girls in the factory

472
00:22:49,390 --> 00:22:53,730
♪ Half of our friends
have left this land ♪

473
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:52,880
avoid us rowdy boys.

474
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,880
But she, whenever she sees us,

475
00:22:54,920 --> 00:22:55,750
grabs her slingshot

476
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:59,280
♪ A pot of wine recalls
our joy and cheer ♪

477
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:57,410
and runs to the Mahavira Hall.

478
00:22:57,700 --> 00:22:59,160
She climbs trees for bird nests,

479
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:00,350
secretly lights firecrackers,

480
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:03,570
♪ Tonight's cold dream
will hold you, my friend dear ♪

481
00:23:00,440 --> 00:23:02,550
and even dares to climb onto truck beds.

482
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:04,410
There's nothing she's afraid of.

483
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:08,950
♪ Far at the edge of sky,
corner of earth ♪

484
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:06,350
But in my heart,

485
00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:08,200
she's one of a kind.

486
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:13,350
♪ Half of our friends
have left this land ♪

487
00:23:11,550 --> 00:23:12,920
Xiaodan looks beautiful when she sings.

488
00:23:12,920 --> 00:23:14,480
Xiaodan looks beautiful all the time.

489
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:18,910
♪ A pot of wine recalls
our joy and cheer ♪

490
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:16,480
You like Xiaodan?

491
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:18,540
What nonsense are you talking about?

492
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:23,350
♪ Tonight's cold dream will hold you,
my friend dear ♪

493
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:20,750
Going to work?

494
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:22,510
No, going to buy groceries.

495
00:23:22,510 --> 00:23:24,160
Ma'am, 25 popsicles please.

496
00:23:39,750 --> 00:23:41,640
One pair, two pairs...

497
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:44,960
That's all of them.

498
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:45,960
Thank you, ma'am.

499
00:23:56,350 --> 00:23:58,270
Ma'am, can I take
these two buckets home first?

500
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:59,750
I'll leave these 5 popsicles here.

501
00:23:59,750 --> 00:24:01,280
-No.
-I'll come back for them soon.

502
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:02,520
But you've left

503
00:24:02,550 --> 00:24:03,270
your tickets here.

504
00:24:03,270 --> 00:24:04,960
You can't just leave this thing here.

505
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:06,000
Ma'am, please.

506
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,270
I can't just abandon it.

507
00:24:07,270 --> 00:24:08,160
I'm just leaving these 5 here.

508
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,160
I'll be back soon.

509
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,160
Why is this kid so indecisive?

510
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,550
Then don't take them at all.

511
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:12,730
It's not the end of the world
if you don't eat them.

512
00:24:12,730 --> 00:24:13,680
Who can't afford a few popsicles?

513
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:14,440
Just take them away.

514
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:15,440
Hurry up. They'll melt soon.

515
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,360
It's been so long.
They're already melting.

516
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,350
Fine if you won't help.

517
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:19,440
I'll figure it out myself.

518
00:24:19,440 --> 00:24:20,350
Seriously.

519
00:24:21,490 --> 00:24:24,380
This kid is so fussy.

520
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:26,510
She won't even help.

521
00:24:28,220 --> 00:24:28,960
Alright, stop checking.

522
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:30,420
-They're all here.
-Okay.

523
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,760
Always so stingy.

524
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:41,400
Hey, kid.

525
00:24:41,510 --> 00:24:42,710
Who are your parents?

526
00:24:42,790 --> 00:24:43,790
Is it too cold for you?

527
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:45,000
It's all because you!

528
00:24:45,400 --> 00:24:46,880
Why are you yelling? What does that have to do with me?

529
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:47,740
Who's yelling?

530
00:24:47,790 --> 00:24:48,720
Speak properly.

531
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,180
This is how I talk. Bite me!

532
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:51,400
I'll tear your mouth apart. You believe me?

533
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,550
Go ahead, try it.

534
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:53,490
Try it, I dare you!

535
00:24:53,490 --> 00:24:54,590
I will! Just watch me!

536
00:24:54,590 --> 00:24:55,590
Come here! Whose brat are you?

537
00:24:55,590 --> 00:24:56,590
Come here!

538
00:24:56,590 --> 00:24:57,110
Don't go! Come!

539
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:57,710
Come here!

540
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:58,720
Come here!

541
00:24:58,720 --> 00:25:01,380
-Come on!
-The White Bone Demon wants to kill me!

542
00:25:08,020 --> 00:25:08,490
Thank you, Grandma.

543
00:25:08,490 --> 00:25:10,010
Try this. See if it's good.

544
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:11,590
So sweet.

545
00:25:13,790 --> 00:25:14,910
Look at you.

546
00:25:14,930 --> 00:25:17,960
It's such a nice fish, and you didn't cook it for the child.

547
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:19,560
You've been drinking all day

548
00:25:20,210 --> 00:25:20,720
What are you saying?

549
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,850
Thank you, Grandma.

550
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,490
If I knew how to cook it, I would.

551
00:25:23,490 --> 00:25:24,690
Then drink less.

552
00:25:24,930 --> 00:25:26,460
Bring the child to my place.

553
00:25:26,470 --> 00:25:27,450
I'll teach you.

554
00:25:27,630 --> 00:25:28,660
Alright.

555
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:30,280
Grandma.

556
00:25:30,290 --> 00:25:31,000
No, no, no.

557
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:31,640
Here.

558
00:25:32,350 --> 00:25:34,460
I prefer the tail.

559
00:25:34,490 --> 00:25:37,480
See? Thick pieces of fish

560
00:25:37,500 --> 00:25:38,350
don't absorb the flavor.

561
00:25:38,350 --> 00:25:40,890
The head and tail taste the best.

562
00:25:42,310 --> 00:25:43,240
Oh, Grandma.

563
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,200
You have no idea.

564
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,200
Today, when I went to get ice cream,

565
00:25:47,200 --> 00:25:49,190
I got into a fight with that person from the collective enterprise.

566
00:25:49,190 --> 00:25:49,880
Why?

567
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:50,490
What?

568
00:25:50,880 --> 00:25:52,540
What collective enterprise?

569
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,600
I'm telling you, that woman—

570
00:25:54,660 --> 00:25:55,640
she was so mean.

571
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:57,330
She had these painted fingernails.

572
00:25:57,330 --> 00:25:58,880
I just asked her to hold my ice cream,

573
00:25:58,880 --> 00:25:59,770
but she wouldn't do it.

574
00:25:59,770 --> 00:26:00,770
She just refused.

575
00:26:01,590 --> 00:26:03,920
So I had to eat 5 popsicles right there.

576
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:04,570
What?

577
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:05,790
Five of them?

578
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,180
Were you crazy?

579
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:10,660
Weren't you afraid of getting diarrhea?

580
00:26:10,940 --> 00:26:12,560
It was fine. I just needed a quick pee.

581
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:13,560
So silly.

582
00:26:13,750 --> 00:26:14,750
Silly.

583
00:26:14,750 --> 00:26:15,610
Zhang Xiaoman.

584
00:26:16,550 --> 00:26:17,550
Let me tell you.

585
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,680
Stop arguing with people all the time.

586
00:26:19,680 --> 00:26:22,330
Be polite to adults.

587
00:26:22,700 --> 00:26:23,500
Got it.

588
00:26:25,680 --> 00:26:26,270
I'll go.

589
00:26:28,280 --> 00:26:29,040
Who is it?

590
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:34,200
Why did you follow me home?

591
00:26:35,350 --> 00:26:36,750
Isn't this Zhang Jiaming's place?

592
00:26:36,750 --> 00:26:37,510
Let me tell you.

593
00:26:37,510 --> 00:26:39,690
Complaining to my dad won't help.

594
00:26:39,710 --> 00:26:40,290
Grandma!

595
00:26:40,310 --> 00:26:41,250
She's the one from the
collective enterprise

596
00:26:41,250 --> 00:26:42,200
-who bullied me!
-Go take a look.

597
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:43,480
Who is it?

598
00:26:47,590 --> 00:26:49,920
Wh-why are you here?

599
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,750
Don't you have work at the office?

600
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:53,680
I just came to drop off some things.

601
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:55,740
You are too polite.

602
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:56,790
Come in.

603
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,530
I finally found this place.

604
00:27:01,160 --> 00:27:02,640
Mom. Come in.

605
00:27:03,970 --> 00:27:06,760
This is my friend, Li.

606
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,240
Hello, ma'am.

607
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:10,720
Well, I got something from my office,

608
00:27:10,720 --> 00:27:12,590
like sausages and apples.

609
00:27:12,590 --> 00:27:13,850
So I brought some over.

610
00:27:13,930 --> 00:27:14,360
Xiaoman.

611
00:27:14,360 --> 00:27:15,030
Thank you.

612
00:27:15,330 --> 00:27:16,790
Put the things over there.

613
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,840
Perfect timing for dinner.

614
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:20,630
Join us.

615
00:27:20,660 --> 00:27:21,580
Don't move.

616
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:22,460
Just sit there.

617
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:25,050
Why is a kid taking up so much space?

618
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:26,340
Come sit with me.

619
00:27:26,370 --> 00:27:27,230
Come, sit here.

620
00:27:28,160 --> 00:27:29,690
I came right at dinnertime.

621
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:31,000
Put my bag over there.

622
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:31,590
Okay.

623
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,520
Have a seat then.

624
00:27:35,410 --> 00:27:36,350
What are you waiting for?

625
00:27:36,350 --> 00:27:38,480
Go get a bowl and chopsticks for Ms. Li.

626
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:40,790
This kid has no awareness at all.

627
00:27:40,790 --> 00:27:43,000
Don't you have hands and legs?

628
00:27:43,290 --> 00:27:45,090
Why keep bossing the kid around?

629
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:49,700
What are you doing?

630
00:27:51,550 --> 00:27:53,550
Dad, get me a different stepmother.

631
00:27:53,790 --> 00:27:55,320
What are you talking about?

632
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,930
How have Grandma and I been teaching you?

633
00:27:57,930 --> 00:27:58,790
She's a demon.

634
00:27:58,790 --> 00:28:00,640
She eats people without spitting out the bones.

635
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,510
Xiaoman.

636
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:04,230
Don't talk to her like that.

637
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:06,940
It's okay, ma'am.

638
00:28:06,960 --> 00:28:07,960
He's immature.

639
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,000
He's just a child.

640
00:28:10,070 --> 00:28:11,880
That being said,

641
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,070
you still have to keep this kid in line.

642
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:13,960
Otherwise,

643
00:28:14,070 --> 00:28:15,750
how are we going to get along

644
00:28:15,750 --> 00:28:18,000
as family?

645
00:28:18,200 --> 00:28:19,590
Who's family with you?

646
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:21,860
Who exactly is your focus in our family?

647
00:28:21,860 --> 00:28:23,110
Me, my grandma, or my dad?

648
00:28:23,110 --> 00:28:24,110
Who are you going to eat?

649
00:28:24,110 --> 00:28:26,570
Zhang Xiaoman, you think I'm being too nice?

650
00:28:26,590 --> 00:28:27,440
Stop it!

651
00:28:28,520 --> 00:28:30,960
Go! Apologize to Ms. Li.

652
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,790
Why should I apologize to her?

653
00:28:32,790 --> 00:28:33,530
What did I do wrong

654
00:28:33,530 --> 00:28:35,260
that I need to apologize to her?

655
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:36,990
I'll teach you a lesson!

656
00:28:37,400 --> 00:28:39,070
What are you doing?

657
00:28:40,730 --> 00:28:41,470
Sit down!

658
00:28:42,510 --> 00:28:44,570
Sit down. You're acting like a child.

659
00:28:44,810 --> 00:28:46,170
Making such a fuss.

660
00:28:46,310 --> 00:28:48,960
That child is young and doesn't know any better. Are you the same?

661
00:28:48,960 --> 00:28:49,960
It's fine, ma'am.

662
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:51,000
I, well...

663
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:52,400
I don't take things personally.

664
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:54,200
I never let these things bother me.

665
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:56,930
It's okay. We will get along better in the future.

666
00:28:58,100 --> 00:28:58,960
Don't be angry.

667
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:12,160
I am Kesai, here to buy vegetables.

668
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,590
Potatoes for 50 cents, greens for 1 yuan.

669
00:29:13,590 --> 00:29:14,400
Time to eat.

670
00:29:19,830 --> 00:29:21,090
Who are you talking to?

671
00:29:21,310 --> 00:29:21,990
No one.

672
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:23,440
Mom, let's go eat.

673
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:26,920
Ma'am?

674
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:28,660
Why are you here?

675
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:31,000
I came to ask Xia Lei to go out and play.

676
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:31,850
Then come in.

677
00:29:32,160 --> 00:29:34,160
No need. I'll just wait for him here.

678
00:29:34,210 --> 00:29:34,750
If you don't come in,

679
00:29:34,750 --> 00:29:35,830
I won't let him go out to play with you.

680
00:29:35,830 --> 00:29:36,570
Did you hear me?

681
00:29:36,570 --> 00:29:37,650
Xiaoman, come.

682
00:29:37,670 --> 00:29:38,550
-Come on.
-Hurry up.

683
00:29:38,550 --> 00:29:39,080
Alright.

684
00:29:39,090 --> 00:29:39,830
Come in.

685
00:29:39,830 --> 00:29:41,570
Don't go this way anymore. It's dangerous.

686
00:29:41,570 --> 00:29:42,610
Alright, ma'am.

687
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,400
This child...

688
00:29:48,930 --> 00:29:50,960
What? Afraid the kids can't wait?

689
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:53,980
You can't even do this?

690
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,280
Ma'am, I don't need this.

691
00:29:58,720 --> 00:29:59,720
What's your name?

692
00:30:00,480 --> 00:30:01,880
My name is Zhang Xiaoman.

693
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:03,600
So you're Xiaoman?

694
00:30:04,270 --> 00:30:06,510
Xia Lei mentions you all the time.

695
00:30:07,590 --> 00:30:08,650
Have you eaten yet?

696
00:30:09,640 --> 00:30:11,470
We eat late at our house.

697
00:30:11,740 --> 00:30:12,740
Time to eat!

698
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:14,830
Then eat at our place.

699
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,070
No need.

700
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:17,400
That won't do.

701
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:19,110
Let me tell you, if you don't eat at our house,

702
00:30:19,110 --> 00:30:20,640
I won't let him go out with you.

703
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:21,400
With you waiting here,

704
00:30:21,400 --> 00:30:22,650
he won't eat properly.

705
00:30:22,650 --> 00:30:23,960
Ma'am, is there anything

706
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,200
I can help you with?

707
00:30:26,110 --> 00:30:27,310
Set up the table then.

708
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:27,830
Okay.

709
00:30:27,910 --> 00:30:28,460
Let's go.

710
00:30:32,350 --> 00:30:33,200
Be careful.

711
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,330
-Be careful.
-Okay.

712
00:30:36,830 --> 00:30:37,480
Help out.

713
00:30:37,720 --> 00:30:38,310
Coming.

714
00:30:39,350 --> 00:30:40,480
Let me wipe it first.

715
00:30:42,590 --> 00:30:44,480
Ma'am, this cloth for wiping the table

716
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:46,400
is cleaner than the one I use to wipe my face.

717
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:47,790
I sterilized it in the pressure cooker.

718
00:30:47,790 --> 00:30:49,000
Ma'am, let me do it.

719
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:49,680
No need.

720
00:30:50,830 --> 00:30:52,030
Just focus on eating.

721
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:55,640
My mom doesn't trust anyone when it comes to cleanliness.

722
00:30:57,350 --> 00:30:58,810
You dad cook at your house?

723
00:30:58,930 --> 00:31:00,130
Yes. What about you?

724
00:31:01,110 --> 00:31:03,830
If my grandma doesn't cook,

725
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:05,590
-my dad does too.
-Put the meat dish here.

726
00:31:05,590 --> 00:31:07,590
Your father cooks at your house too?

727
00:31:07,960 --> 00:31:09,090
What about your mom?

728
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:10,030
My mom...

729
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:12,050
isn't home.

730
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:18,210
Look at those big bites.

731
00:31:18,590 --> 00:31:19,200
Really.

732
00:31:19,220 --> 00:31:19,970
Eat slower.

733
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:21,100
Or you'll get indigestion.

734
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:22,800
Uncle, your cooking is amazing.

735
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:23,550
-Tasty, right?
-Eat slowly.

736
00:31:23,550 --> 00:31:24,270
I have soup over there.

737
00:31:24,270 --> 00:31:24,940
When the soup is ready,

738
00:31:24,940 --> 00:31:26,540
have some. Don't choke on it.

739
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:40,270
Fire!

740
00:31:44,640 --> 00:31:45,640
You're cheating!

741
00:31:46,150 --> 00:31:47,460
Go! Wang Dongdong!

742
00:31:48,750 --> 00:31:49,720
I won!

743
00:32:04,660 --> 00:32:05,690
Let me tell you.

744
00:32:05,830 --> 00:32:07,070
I've looked into it.

745
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:09,260
Making money there is super easy.

746
00:32:09,270 --> 00:32:11,160
It's about 3 days by train.

747
00:32:11,350 --> 00:32:13,550
Once everything's arranged, let's go.

748
00:32:16,380 --> 00:32:17,140
Who is it?

749
00:32:18,880 --> 00:32:19,810
Someone's back?

750
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:20,960
Xiaoman?

751
00:32:21,290 --> 00:32:23,200
Didn't you say he went to his grandma's?

752
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,270
He has a key.

753
00:32:24,640 --> 00:32:25,840
How does he have a key?

754
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:28,050
It's his home. How can he not have a key?

755
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:31,970
You go.

756
00:32:32,830 --> 00:32:33,690
Go check it out.

757
00:32:33,870 --> 00:32:34,670
Me?

758
00:32:34,690 --> 00:32:36,640
He's your son, and you want me to check?
You go ahead.

759
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,270
Fine.

760
00:32:39,410 --> 00:32:40,830
Come on. Seriously.

761
00:32:40,830 --> 00:32:41,710
Don't worry.

762
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,700
Xiaoman, you're back?

763
00:32:52,790 --> 00:32:54,590
Didn't you go to your grandma's?

764
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:56,260
Xiaoman, you're back?

765
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:57,710
Are you hungry?

766
00:32:57,710 --> 00:32:58,570
What do you want for dinner?

767
00:32:58,570 --> 00:32:59,570
I'll buy something and cook for you.

768
00:32:59,570 --> 00:33:00,430
I'm not eating.

769
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:01,830
Not hungry?

770
00:33:02,360 --> 00:33:03,020
Not hungry.

771
00:33:04,030 --> 00:33:05,110
Then don't eat.

772
00:33:05,140 --> 00:33:06,180
Fine.

773
00:33:06,480 --> 00:33:07,270
That attitude.

774
00:33:07,270 --> 00:33:08,270
Tough guy.

775
00:33:08,780 --> 00:33:10,320
I wonder if you're this tough

776
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:11,750
when it comes to studying.

777
00:33:11,750 --> 00:33:12,480
What did you score?

778
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:13,940
Did you get perfect marks?

779
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:16,100
Did you get perfect marks?

780
00:33:20,740 --> 00:33:22,600
What do you want? I'll go buy some.

781
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:24,440
Anything is fine.

782
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,240
Braised ribs?

783
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:26,650
I make great ribs.

784
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,660
Don't make it too complicated.

785
00:33:28,660 --> 00:33:29,520
Keep it simple.

786
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:30,830
Let me tell you.

787
00:33:30,830 --> 00:33:32,770
Ribs braised with beans are so good.

788
00:33:32,770 --> 00:33:33,230
Wait...

789
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:36,100
Soybean paste?

790
00:33:37,830 --> 00:33:39,720
Look at this. It's all sticky!

791
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:42,500
Soybean paste!

792
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:44,680
Was it you?

793
00:33:44,840 --> 00:33:45,550
It wasn't me!

794
00:33:45,550 --> 00:33:46,440
You dare say it wasn't you?

795
00:33:46,440 --> 00:33:47,550
It really wasn't me!

796
00:33:47,550 --> 00:33:48,720
Where did the paste come from then?

797
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:50,030
I don't know!

798
00:33:51,290 --> 00:33:52,440
It really wasn't me, Dad.

799
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:53,200
Apologize to Mrs. Li.

800
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,000
Do you hear me?

801
00:33:54,030 --> 00:33:55,130
Apologize to her. Do you hear me?

802
00:33:55,130 --> 00:33:55,930
Do you hear me?

803
00:33:56,030 --> 00:33:57,830
It wasn't me. Why should I apologize?

804
00:33:57,830 --> 00:33:58,830
Stop hitting him.

805
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:00,160
Grandma, easy.

806
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:01,030
Hold on.

807
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:02,350
He hit me so hard.

808
00:34:02,370 --> 00:34:04,100
My dad didn't control himself.

809
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:08,070
Why did you have to provoke that woman?

810
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:09,440
Whether I provoked her or not,

811
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,070
she doesn't like me anyway.

812
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:16,659
Grandma, I don't want to go home tonight.

813
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:18,989
Then don't.

814
00:34:19,280 --> 00:34:20,280
Stay here with me.

815
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,929
Let's see if your dad will get worried.

816
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:25,510
Grandma,

817
00:34:26,270 --> 00:34:29,330
when Dad was little, did Grandpa beat him like this too?

818
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:31,360
Of course not.

819
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:34,150
Your grandpa adored your dad.

820
00:34:35,190 --> 00:34:37,210
I was the one who did the beating.

821
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,469
So do I take after Grandpa or Dad?

822
00:34:39,710 --> 00:34:40,480
You...

823
00:34:42,230 --> 00:34:43,489
are like your grandpa.

824
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:47,440
All those good qualities your grandpa had

825
00:34:47,460 --> 00:34:50,860
skipped a generation and went to my grandson.

826
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:54,510
Grandma,

827
00:34:55,230 --> 00:34:57,400
did Grandpa really fight in two of the Three Major Campaigns?

828
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,070
Yes.

829
00:34:58,560 --> 00:35:01,290
The Liaoshen and Pingjin campaigns—

830
00:35:01,630 --> 00:35:02,830
he was in both of them.

831
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:05,230
He even fought in the Korean War.

832
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:06,290
Alright.

833
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:07,630
Did he have a gun?

834
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:09,630
Of course.

835
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,880
He used all kinds of guns.

836
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:15,360
Type 55, Type 81,

837
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:18,180
semi-auto, full-auto,

838
00:35:18,210 --> 00:35:19,330
"turtle box,"

839
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:20,880
and "Dujuezi".

840
00:35:21,840 --> 00:35:22,630
"Dujuezi"?

841
00:35:23,230 --> 00:35:24,360
What's a "Dujuezi"?

842
00:35:24,670 --> 00:35:27,550
A Dujuezi is homemade

843
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:29,440
and shoots one shot at a time.

844
00:35:29,580 --> 00:35:30,710
But that was enough.

845
00:35:33,110 --> 00:35:34,630
Where are those guns now?

846
00:35:35,310 --> 00:35:37,770
They were all handed over to the government.

847
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:38,840
Grandpa must've

848
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:40,840
killed a lot of reactionaries back then.

849
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:42,360
I don't know about that.

850
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,030
But your grandpa

851
00:35:44,030 --> 00:35:46,630
never missed a battle he was supposed to fight.

852
00:35:47,150 --> 00:35:48,470
Grandpa was really something.

853
00:35:48,470 --> 00:35:50,390
Grandma, I'm going out to play.

854
00:35:51,410 --> 00:35:53,160
What about your injury?

855
00:35:53,230 --> 00:35:53,840
It's fine.

856
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:54,480
I take after Grandpa. I don't feel pain.

857
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:55,840
Come back early, alright?

858
00:35:55,840 --> 00:35:56,670
Alright!

859
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:58,440
Such a tough kid.

860
00:36:01,380 --> 00:36:02,380
You...

861
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,710
You were so capable.

862
00:36:05,230 --> 00:36:07,830
How come your son doesn't take after you at all?

863
00:36:08,730 --> 00:36:09,370
You

864
00:36:09,990 --> 00:36:11,720
should just bless our grandson

865
00:36:12,890 --> 00:36:16,250
and keep him safe for his whole life.

866
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:25,280
Books!

867
00:36:25,710 --> 00:36:26,550
Alright.

868
00:36:26,550 --> 00:36:28,110
Stop fooling around. Class is starting.

869
00:36:28,110 --> 00:36:29,240
The teacher's here.

870
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:31,280
The teacher's here.

871
00:36:33,270 --> 00:36:34,800
Okay, hurry up and sit down.

872
00:36:35,180 --> 00:36:37,730
Now, before class,

873
00:36:38,110 --> 00:36:39,800
I need to announce something.

874
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:43,550
We're going to select the model student for this semester.

875
00:36:43,550 --> 00:36:45,280
Who would you like to nominate?

876
00:36:45,760 --> 00:36:47,490
You can make your suggestions.

877
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:49,670
I nominate Zhang Wei.

878
00:36:49,760 --> 00:36:50,880
Okay, Zhang Wei.

879
00:36:51,920 --> 00:36:52,650
Anyone else?

880
00:36:53,150 --> 00:36:54,480
I nominate Li Xiaohong.

881
00:36:55,070 --> 00:36:55,800
Anyone else?

882
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:57,230
I nominate Mo Xixi.

883
00:37:00,440 --> 00:37:01,100
That's all?

884
00:37:01,960 --> 00:37:04,510
Ma'am, I nominate Xia Lei!

885
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:06,790
Xiaoman, can you stop messing around?

886
00:37:06,790 --> 00:37:09,590
Only those who are surrendering raise both hands.

887
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:12,010
Who raises both hands to nominate someone?

888
00:37:12,010 --> 00:37:12,700
Okay.

889
00:37:13,420 --> 00:37:14,120
Xia Lei.

890
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:26,090
You're back?

891
00:37:29,260 --> 00:37:30,660
Why did you bring it back?

892
00:37:31,250 --> 00:37:32,650
You didn't give it to her?

893
00:37:34,670 --> 00:37:35,730
She didn't take it.

894
00:37:39,550 --> 00:37:40,950
What did the teacher say?

895
00:37:40,950 --> 00:37:43,030
Nothing. She was quite nice.

896
00:37:43,190 --> 00:37:44,920
She said that first,

897
00:37:45,250 --> 00:37:46,960
teachers aren't allowed to accept gifts.

898
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:48,090
And second, well...

899
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:49,590
Xia Lei himself,

900
00:37:49,590 --> 00:37:51,360
his interpersonal relationships...

901
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:53,510
He only gets along well with Xiaoman.

902
00:37:53,530 --> 00:37:55,660
He doesn't get along with other classmates.

903
00:37:55,660 --> 00:37:57,070
So it's not appropriate to give him that.

904
00:37:57,070 --> 00:37:58,730
She said she'll see next year.

905
00:37:59,150 --> 00:38:00,150
She had a point.

906
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:01,680
What point?

907
00:38:02,100 --> 00:38:05,430
Our kid gets perfect scores in every subject.

908
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:08,150
At his old school, he was a model student every year.

909
00:38:08,150 --> 00:38:09,670
Now he didn't get it this year.

910
00:38:09,670 --> 00:38:11,360
What if he loses

911
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,280
his motivation to study?

912
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:16,480
It'll affect his college entrance exam in the future.

913
00:38:16,550 --> 00:38:17,630
You have a point too.

914
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:19,360
But that's a bit exaggerated.

915
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,360
Exaggerated? You don't understand.

916
00:38:21,360 --> 00:38:22,710
Our kid is in

917
00:38:22,730 --> 00:38:24,450
a very important stage.

918
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:26,320
This is when independent learning awareness

919
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:27,520
is being cultivated.

920
00:38:29,550 --> 00:38:31,360
What are you doing? You scared me.

921
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:31,840
Wait.

922
00:38:35,190 --> 00:38:36,350
Why did you come?

923
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,510
I came to see you.

924
00:38:37,770 --> 00:38:38,880
Not selecting you as the model student

925
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:40,280
shows they have no taste.

926
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:43,840
Here.

927
00:38:43,950 --> 00:38:44,810
I don't want it.

928
00:38:45,100 --> 00:38:45,710
Take it.

929
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:48,730
Anyway, in my heart you're the best.

930
00:38:48,730 --> 00:38:50,190
You're the model student.

931
00:38:50,190 --> 00:38:51,290
I'm leaving now.

932
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:53,720
I'll go back home

933
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:55,980
I'll take you to the bathhouse tomorrow.

934
00:39:09,070 --> 00:39:10,760
Two more, Dad.

935
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,150
More?

936
00:39:12,910 --> 00:39:14,150
One last one.

937
00:39:14,150 --> 00:39:15,150
Please.

938
00:40:24,030 --> 00:40:25,960
I'm exhausted. Let's take a break.

939
00:40:27,150 --> 00:40:29,110
My dad's making stewed ribs for me tonight.

940
00:40:29,110 --> 00:40:30,640
Come to my place for dinner.

941
00:40:30,840 --> 00:40:31,440
No thanks.

942
00:40:31,710 --> 00:40:34,480
My grandma specially steamed bean buns and is waiting for me.

943
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:35,630
Your grandma is so nice.

944
00:40:35,630 --> 00:40:37,160
Why don't you live with her?

945
00:40:37,670 --> 00:40:39,530
Then my dad would be living alone.

946
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:44,880
When my dad's not hitting me, he's actually pretty good.

947
00:40:44,880 --> 00:40:47,070
Recently he's been playing harmonica for me.

948
00:40:47,070 --> 00:40:49,000
Maybe he's changed for the better.

949
00:40:58,290 --> 00:41:00,220
Grandma, why aren't the lights on?

950
00:41:01,890 --> 00:41:03,220
I'm not doing anything.

951
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:05,170
Why waste electricity?

952
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:06,630
Where's my dad?

953
00:41:07,550 --> 00:41:08,670
Your dad left.

954
00:41:09,890 --> 00:41:11,640
He went south with that demon.

955
00:41:13,110 --> 00:41:14,400
He left you a note.

956
00:41:15,830 --> 00:41:16,430
Let me see.

957
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,110
Xiaoman,

958
00:41:25,670 --> 00:41:26,400
I'm leaving.

959
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:30,280
I wanted to wait until you grew up to do this.

960
00:41:32,320 --> 00:41:34,030
But that's how life is.

961
00:41:35,670 --> 00:41:37,530
East Chemical Plant is too small.

962
00:41:38,550 --> 00:41:41,010
I don't want to be trapped here my whole life.

963
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:42,960
I want to go out

964
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:45,260
and see the world outside.

965
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,610
Live well with Grandma.

966
00:41:48,590 --> 00:41:49,630
Listen to her.

967
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:53,210
When I make something of myself out there,

968
00:41:54,290 --> 00:41:56,550
I'll come back to pick you and Grandma up.

969
00:42:20,590 --> 00:42:21,360
Xiaoman.

970
00:42:22,070 --> 00:42:23,510
You don't need to bring so many things

971
00:42:23,510 --> 00:42:24,960
to my place to live.

972
00:42:26,150 --> 00:42:27,030
Alright, Grandma.

973
00:42:27,030 --> 00:42:28,490
I'll be done packing soon.

974
00:42:51,930 --> 00:42:53,130
Grandma, be careful.

975
00:42:55,570 --> 00:42:56,400
Be careful, Grandma.
